metadata.name: Tumbling Six #23
metadata.description:
Six hollow cubes tumbling through space quietly, enjoying their six degrees of freedom. Only a single machine is there to bear witness. It is Sentinel 31, and its mind wanders. Distracted, it recreates the scene, drawing imaginary lines with an imaginary hand.

~

The original medium of Tumbling Six is the pen plotter. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG, and rely on Three.js for spatial modeling.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. The plottable SVG does not include the light grey sketch lines that appear at the start of the animation. Those look nice on screen, but are too much include on paper.

metadata.name: Lime Brass Hyacinth #31
metadata.description: "Lime Brass Hyacinth" is a p5.js project where isometric shapes are placed and have their size and color adjusted based on an underlying grid of gradients. Each form is derived from the lightness or darkness of a particular pixel in the underlying grid. Many renders remind me of cityscapes with buildings, roads, and bridges.

metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #345
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.
